  "title": "Management Associate Program",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide consultancy services to our corporate and individual clients.</p></li><li><p>Enhance our clientele base through business developments & strategies.</p></li><li><p>Assist the management in organizing events and corporate networking.</p></li><li><p>Managing team performance to meet company’s expectations.<br /> </p></li></ul><p><strong>Training & Benefits:</strong></p><p>Selected candidates will go through a comprehensive set of training to excel in various departments as well as leadership skills to form part of our management team. This provides great exposure for future management of departments.</p><ul><li><p>Candidate must already have or currently pursuing at least a Diploma or Degree in Business, Marketing, Finance or equivalent.</p></li><li><p>Candidate must possess qualities of versatility, resilience and willingness to learn.</p></li><li><p>Candidates without experience are still welcome and encouraged to apply.</p></li><li><p>Singaporeans and Permanent Residents  only.</p></li><li><p>3 Full time position(s) available.<br /> </p></li></ul><p><strong>You will be exposed to the following areas:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Attractive remuneration package with bonus & incentives.</p></li><li><p>Step-by-step career progression and personal development opportunities.</p></li><li><p>Development of excellent management and leadership skills.</p></li><li><p>All training will be provided.</p></li><li><p>One to one career mentoring with experienced industry leaders.</p></li></ul><p>Note: We currently do not have quota for visas<br /></p><p><strong>Job Type: Full-time</strong></p><p>Pay: $3,500.00 - $6,000.00 per month<br /></p><p><strong>Schedule:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Monday to Friday</p></li></ul><p><strong>Education:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum Local Polytechnic Diploma (Required)</p></li></ul><p></p>",
